cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising using deep neural networks. The use of machine learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a new perceptual similarity measure as the objective function could suggest that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of CT images could suggest that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with medical imaging.
